description: The suspended JD(S) functionary and Hassan MP Prajwal Revanna, who is the grandson of former Prime Minister HD Deve Gowda, has been issued a lookout notice by a special investigation team on Thursday. Prajwal is currently involved in a case related to an alleged sex video. The special investigation team has also summoned Prajwal and his father, HD Revanna, to appear for questioning in connection with the case.
title: Obscene video case: Lookout notice for ex-PM Deve Gowda's grandson Prajwal Revanna

description: Supreme Court addressed Centre's objections to West Bengal's lawsuit over CBI investigations post consent withdrawal. Tushar Mehta highlighted misuse of Article 131. West Bengal withdrew consent in November 2018.
title: 'CBI not under Union govt's control': Centre to SC on Bengal govt's lawsuit

description: The UAE is currently experiencing severe weather conditions, prompting the issuance of an orange alert. Heavy rains and thunderstorms have engulfed the region, disrupting normal life and leading to a series of precautionary measures. On Thursday, as the unstable weather reached its peak, residents were advised to stay indoors, and remote work was enforced across both public and private sectors.
title: Flights cancelled, resident told to stay indoors: UAE faces heavy rains again

description: In a letter addressed to Prime Minister Narendra Modi, Mallikarjun Kharge, the Congress chief, expressed his concerns regarding the Prime Minister's recent communication to NDA candidates. Kharge pointed out that the language employed in the letter seemed to reflect a sense of desperation and anxiety, which he deemed inappropriate for the esteemed office of the Prime Minister.
title: 'Our votebank is every Indian': Kharge writes to PM Modi

description: Former Indian cricketer Madan Lal has named Rishabh Pant as a potential game-changer for Rohit Sharma's Indian team for the upcoming T20 World Cup. Lal believes India could dominate the tournament if Pant is in front. Lal praised Pant's comeback and said India's success depends on his performance, team position, and usage. Pant is considered one of the top batsmen globally.
title: Ex-WC winner reveals the X-factor of Rohit-led Indian team

description: Deepak Gupta, a 32-year-old fitness enthusiast, tragically died after experiencing a severe headache while at a gym in Varanasi on Wednesday. CCTV footage captured Gupta holding his head, trembling, and receiving assistance from others. Despite being rushed to a medical facility, he was pronounced dead upon arrival. Gupta had been a dedicated gym-goer for the past decade.
title: 32-year-old man dies during workout at Varanasi gym

description: Micron India aims to release semiconductor chips packaged at its Sanand facility in Gujarat for export by early next year. The company plans to cater to global demand for chips, with a focus on data centers, smartphones, notebooks, IoT devices, and automotive segments.
title: Micron to export 1st batch of India-made semiconductor chips in '25

description: Demand for Akhilesh Yadav, Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, and Rahul Gandhi in UP for public meetings. Joint meetings requested for alliance cohesiveness. Imran Pratapgarhi, Pramod Tewari, and Sanjay Singh are popular campaigners.
title: Akhilesh in high demand for poll campaign among Cong candidates

description: Punjab Kings won the Indian Premier League match against Chennai Super Kings on Wednesday, extending their winning streak and sparking a playful exchange around the 'Thala for a reason' meme. Their witty social media presence, featuring references to the meme, stole the spotlight during the match. The match was a testament to PBKS' dominance.
title: 'Thala for a reason': Punjab's banter sparks social media frenzy

description: Mahindra XUV 3XO and Tata Nexon compete in the compact SUV segment. The XUV 3XO offers competitive pricing, segment-first features like a panoramic sunroof and ADAS suite, advanced infotainment system, and various premium features.
title: Mahindra XUV 3XO vs Tata Nexon: Which one offers better prices, features

description: As the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test (NEET) Undergraduate (UG) exam date approaches, students across the country face a significant hurdle in downloading their admit cards due to technical glitches. Despite the availability of the admit card link, a substantial number of aspirants remain unable to access this crucial document necessary for appearing in the exam. This synopsis delves into the underlying reasons behind this persistent issue.
title: NEET UG admit card: Students still unable to download, here's why

description: Maruti Suzuki India plans to sell approximately 2 million vehicles this fiscal year, aiming to surpass the domestic industry. The company's targeted growth exceeds industry projections, driven by new model launches such as Swift and Dzire.
title: Maruti Suzuki car bets on new generation Swift and Dzire models

description: Former Indian cricketer Irfan Pathan has criticized MS Dhoni's decision-making during Chennai Super Kings' match against Punjab Kings. Pathan criticized Dhoni's approach towards strike rotation and struggles against spin bowling. He also criticized Dhoni's treatment of New Zealand batter Daryl Mitchell, arguing it was a team game and he should not have done so.
title: Ex-India player questions Dhoni's decision not to take 'singles'

description: India is considering allowing Chinese electronics firms to invest on a case-by-case basis. The Ministry of Electronics and IT has reached out to Shanghai Highly for investment strategies, signaling a shift in policy. Indian companies, like Voltas, are seeking partnerships amidst regulatory hurdles.
title: India may ease curbs on Chinese investment in hi-tech electronics

description: Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena has directed the immediate dismissal of 223 Delhi Women's Commission employees. These individuals were recruited by ex-chairperson Swati Maliwal, allegedly without proper approvals, breaching established protocols.
title: LG VK Saxena sacks 223 employees of Delhi women's commission

description: Tamil playback singer Uma Ramanan, known for 'Poongathave Thal Thiravai', passed away at 72. Her demise led to mourning on social media. Uma Ramanan's husband requested a private funeral, expressing deep sorrow.
title: Popular playback singer Uma Ramanan passes away

description: Kohli, with a tally of 500 runs for RCB in this IPL season so far, surrendered his leading position as run-getter and the Orange Cap to CSK captain Ruturaj Gaikwad, whose tally of runs has surged to 509. Despite this, with four matches still left to play, Kohli remains in contention to regain the Orange Cap.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli passes the 'A to Z' test

description: Joe Biden stated on Wednesday that India, China, Russia, and Japan are struggling economically because "they're xenophobic" and "don't want immigrants". ​"Why is China stalling so badly economically, why is Japan having trouble, why is Russia, why is India, because they're xenophobic. They don't want immigrants. Immigrants are what makes us strong," Biden said.
title: 'Xenophobia' stalling India, China, Japan economic growth: Biden

description: Google laid off 200 employees from Core teams, relocating roles to India and Mexico. Part of downsizing effort impacting online safety, Python tools, app platforms. Asim Husain and Pankaj Rohatgi commented on expansion.
title: Google cuts jobs in ‘Core team’: What top executives told employees

description: India supports Palestine's UN membership bid, hoping for reconsideration. Backs two-state solution. Palestine holds non-member observer status. Conflict casualties rise. India provides humanitarian aid to Gaza.
title: India backs two-state solution where Palestinians can live freely

description: Decision pending on Gandhi siblings' UP contest. Media speculates Rahul may skip Amethi. State unit urges traditional seat contest. Concerns about leaving Wayanad. Rahul's travel plans. Priyanka tours Chhattisgarh, MP. BJP delays candidate announcement.
title: Congress maintains suspense on Amethi, Rae Bareli choice

description: Comedian Shyam Rangeela, famous for mimicry, to contest Lok Sabha elections from Varanasi. He plans to challenge PM Modi, providing voters with an alternative option. Born in Rajasthan, he gained popularity through social media.
title: Who is Shyam Rangeela? Once a Modi fan, now contesting against PM

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, gained in trade on Thursday. While BSE Sensex moved up over 150 points, Nifty50 was near 22,650.
title: Sensex up 150 points; Nifty50 near 22,650

description: Former India cricketer K Srikkanth has criticized the BCCI for overlooking Ruturaj Gaikwad in the T20 World Cup 2024 squad selection, despite his stellar performances. Srikkanth argued that Gaikwad deserves a place, having scored over 500 runs in 17 T20I innings and a century against Australia, highlighting concerns of favoritism and biased selection practices.
title: T20 WC: Ex-India player slams BCCI for 'biased' selection

description: WhatsApp launches event creation for groups with RSVP, timely notifications, and replies feature. Testing account restriction for violators to limit messaging capabilities while allowing essential communication.
title: WhatsApp rolls out new way to organise events: Here’s what it is and more

description: Goldy Brar, the notorious Canadian gangster, is confirmed alive by US authorities, contrary to reports of his death circulating on Tuesday. The Fresno Police Department dismissed the rumors, stating they were "untrue."
title: Notorious gangster Goldy Brar is alive: US cops

description: NEET applicant with special needs granted permission by Madras high court to wear a diaper and change it as required during the NEET-UG exam, ensuring equal opportunities for all candidates.
title: Madras HC allows girl to use diaper during NEET exam on May 5

description: Comedian Shyam Rangeela to contest against PM Modi in Varanasi Lok Sabha constituency as an Independent candidate. He plans to share his election journey through a video and will visit Varanasi for filing nomination, with elections scheduled for June 1.
title: Comedian Shyam Rangeela to contest against PM Modi in Varanasi

description: RR skipper Sanju Samson, setting a stellar example for the team in this IPL season, has earned a spot in India's T20 World Cup squad as the second wicketkeeper-batsman alongside Rishabh Pant. Samson sits at No. 7 currently on the list of top run-getters of IPL 2024 with 385 runs in 9 matches, including four half-centuries.
title: Watch: IPL teammates hail 'Chintu bro' for India comeback

description: Suspended JD(S) functionary Prajwal Revanna, embroiled in sex video case, to return from Germany on May 3-4, breaking silence. CID in contact, CM wrote to PM. Visit followed Lok Sabha polls.
title: Sex tapes case: Prajwal may return from Germany this weekend

description: Amazon Great Summer Sale offers irresistible discounts on a wide range of smartphones for Prime and non-Prime members. From OnePlus to Apple, Samsung, iQoo, Realme, and Xiaomi, there are amazing deals waiting for every tech enthusiast.
title: Amazon Great Summer Sale: Non-to-miss deals on smartphones

description: Shivam Dube's exceptional performance in various tournaments, backed by Mumbai's Raju Kulkarni, led to his selection in India's T20 World Cup squad after a career turnaround highlighted by impressive displays in IPL and domestic cricket. During the 2022-23 domestic season, Dube played a vital part in Mumbai's Syed Mushtaq Ali T20 triumph (186 runs in 10 matches@62.00 & eight wickets@22.87) but Dube didn't get to play a game in either the Vijay Hazare Trophy or the Ranji Trophy.
title: Shivam Dube: From Mumbai snub to India's T20 World Cup squad

description: From the East Coast to Texas and the capital, protesters are calling on educational institutions to cut financial connections with Israel and provide amnesty to students who have violated regulations, among other demands. The standoffs have elicited both criticism and backing from elected officials, academic staff, and wealthy benefactors. As graduation ceremonies draw near, administrators find themselves under mounting pressure to address the situation.
title: US campuses on edge; hundreds arrested: Top developments

description: Rishabh Pant discussed the importance of ambition, dreams, and the journey of cricket in a candid interview. He emphasized the transformative nature of aspirations, which can range from childhood fantasies to self-motivated milestones. Pant's resilience and determination are evident in his ability to see the evolution of dreams and their importance in shaping one's life.
title: Playing for India is not a destination, it's a journey: Pant

description: Rohingya refugee children from Hyderabad secure scholarships to study at top US and Canadian universities, with dreams of uplifting their community. Shaik Usman, among others, aims to pursue medicine and return to help his people in Bangladesh.
title: In a first, refugee Rohingya kids from Hyderabad all set to study in top US varsities

description: Unrest in Ladakh affects BJP's election. Gyalson replaces Namgyal. People demand legislative assembly. Wangchuk led hunger strike. Ladakh now separate Union Territory without legislature, causing disillusionment among residents.
title: Despite candidate change, it’s still an uphill task for BJP in Ladakh

description: Harshal Patel, who was celebrating a crucial catch, mimicked Yuzvendra Chahal's signature pose during an IPL match between Chennai Super Kings and Punjab Kings. Chahal humorously addressed Patel and suggested seeking copyright protection for his unique pose. The incident caught Chahal's attention and sparked a humorous response on social media.
title: 'Elon paaji...': Chahal's funny response after Patel imitates his pose

description: Kolkata Knight Riders mentor Gautam Gambhir, a former India opening batter, praised Chennai Super Kings for using MS Dhoni's exceptional skills in the Indian Premier League 2024. Gambhir praised CSK's tactical approach, particularly assigning Dhoni the finisher role with just 8-10 balls, which allowed Dhoni to make an immediate impact.
title: 'Freedom': Gambhir explains CSK's Dhoni strategy in IPL 2024

description: Amidst shifting political landscapes in Malda, the legacy of Barkat da and ABA Ghani Khan Chowdhury remains influential. The battle for Malda North intensifies with new candidates emerging, challenging established family legacies and political affiliations.
title: 40 yrs on, BJP & TMC threaten to breach Ghani fort

BJPs chances in North Karnataka hinge on that

description: Alphabet's Chief Executive Officer, Sundar Pichai, is close to reaching a significant achievement for a technology executive who is not a founder: a fortune worth ten figures. Since Sundar Pichai, who is 51 years old, took over as the Chief Executive Officer of Google in 2015, the stock price has increased by over 400%, showing significant outperformance compared to the S&P and Nasdaq during the same timeframe.
title: Google CEO Pichai nears billionaire status
